Error: Error: "Cannot Allocate Enough Memory For The Java Virtual Machine"

Step-By-Step

Solution: 1. Log in to your Pterodactyl Panel.
2. Click on the Minecraft Server you want to configure.
3. Click on the "Console" tab at the top of the page.
4. Check the current memory allocation by running the command: "java -Xmx". 
   The '-Xmx' flag sets the maximum amount of memory that the JVM will use.
5. Allocate
